<blockquote>[anchor=twopointthree]
[center][size=12pt][b][2300] = Making Rewards Work[/b][/size][/center]</blockquote>

Add this underneath boolean process (client.java)
Before I give you it, many ask why I made you declare "AxeScore". Well it's to prevent people from getting the same reward again and again. You see later on, we will make chests in the area that reset your score. So if you want to get the same reward again, you would reset your current score and do it again. This is why we use the AxeScore integer to keep count to prevent people from getting the same reward again and again.
[code=java]
		if(isInAxeKilla()) { // if the person is in axekilla (check the boolean in step 1)
		AxePanel1(); // call out the axe panel method
                if(AxeKilled == 20 || AxeKilled == 21 || AxeKilled == 22 || AxeKilled == 23) { // if the person has the following scores...
                    if(AxeScore == 0) { // and the person's score is zero...
                        addItem(995, 10000000); // add 10M
                        sM("You have just won 10M for 20 axes Killed!"); // send a message
                        AxeScore = 1; // set the score to one. 
                }
    } else if(AxeKilled == 50 || AxeKilled == 51 || AxeKilled == 52 || AxeKilled == 53) { // if the person has the following scores...
                    if(AxeScore == 1) { // and the person's score is one...
                        addItem(995, 30000000); // add 30M
                        sM("You have just won 30M for 50 axes Killed!"); // send a message
                        AxeScore = 2; // set the score to two
                }
    } else if(AxeKilled == 100 || AxeKilled == 101 || AxeKilled == 102 || AxeKilled == 103) { // if the person has the following scores....
                    if(AxeScore == 2) { // and the person's score is two...
                        addItem(660, 1); // add all of this 3rd age mage crap
