[center][size=12pt][b][2400] = NPCHandler, PlayerHandler, textHandler and clickingmost[/b][/size][/center]</blockquote>

In NPCHandler.java, boolean process, add this
[code=java]
if (npcs[i].npcType == 127) { // if killed NPCID 127 (magic axe)
PlayerHandler.AxeKilled += 1; // add 1 to AxeKilled in PlayerHandler
temp.AxeKilled += 1 + misc.random(2); // add + 1-3 to AxeKilled in client.java
} // end the if condition[/code]

Now for the very easy part. The easiest part of this tutorial. Go into PlayerHandler.java and declare this somewhere at the top
[code=java]
public static int AxeKilled = 0; // declaring a static integer in PlayerHandler called "AxeKilled" and setting it's value to 0[/code]

Now go into textHandler.java and add this
[code=java]
if(c.q4 == 0){ // if the player hasn't started quest no. 4:
c.sendQuest("Axe Killer", 7336); // set the text "7336" to "Axe Killer"
}
if(c.q4 > 0){ // if the player has started quest no. 4: 
c.sendQuest("@yel@Axe Killer", 7336); // set the text "7336" to "Axe Killer" in yellow
}
if(c.q4 == 15){ // if the player has finished quest no. 4:
c.sendQuest("@gre@Axe Killer", 7336); // set the text "7336" to "Axe Killer" in green
}[/code]
Everyone will atleast have not started, started, or finished quest number 4. That's why we added conditions to add some colour to the text.

Go into clickingmost.java and add this case somewhere
[code=java]
case 28168: // the button ID for the "Axe Killer" text
c.triggerTele(3414, 3488, 0); // teleport the player to X-3414, Y-3488 and Height-0
break; // close the case[/code]
