In client.java, add this underneath case 132 (packet that checks object's being clicked)
[code=java]
if (objectID == 75) { // if clicked on object 75
	NpcDialogue = 163; // set the NpcDialogue to 163
	NpcDialogueSend = false; 
} // end if object 75 clicked statement[/code]Now under [code=java]
switch (NpcDialogue) {[/code]
Add this:
[code=java]
case 163: // checking if npcdialogue is 163
	choice("Yes, reset my Axe Killed points", "No, I want to keep my points"); // give two choices
	break; // end case 163[/code]
We are almost finished! Now we just have to make that choice button work.
Go into clickingmost for the last time and underneath case 9157, add this
[code=java]
if(c.NpcDialogue == 163){ // if the player is currently in case 9157 (clicking the first option in the choice menu) and the dialogue is 163...
c.closeAll(); // close all interfaces
c.AxeScore = 0; // set axescore to 0 so the person can get their rewards again
c.AxeKilled = 0; // set axekilled to 0 so the person can kill more axes again
} // end checking if dialogue is 163 in clickingmost[/code]
