<blockquote>[anchor=glossary]
[center][size=20pt][b]Glossary[/b][/size][/center]</blockquote>

[hr]

[color=blue][b]Word:[/b] Axe points 
[color=green][b]Definition:[/b] points earned after killing a magic axe (ID = 127)

[hr]

[color=blue][b]Word:[/b] Rewards
[color=green][b]Definition:[/b] An item(s) that a player would recieve if the player has achieved a specific amount of axe points and axe score required. The only possible rewards are listed below

20 Axe points = 10M Gp
50 Axe points = 30M Gp
100 Axe points = Full 3rd Age Mage
150 Axe points = 100M Gp
300 Axe points = Fighter torso
500 Axe points = Sled
700 Axe points = Santa Hat
800 Axe points = Bow-Sword
1000 Axe points = 1B Gp
2000 Axe points = Godsword Hilt Set

[hr]

[color=blue][b]Word:[/b] Declare
[color=green][b]Definition:[/b] To create a new item in java. Mostly used as in creating a new "void", "boolean", or "int". This new item can then be used or called out later on in a java program.

[hr]

[color=blue][b]Word:[/b] Boolean
[color=green][b]Definition:[/b] A variable in java that can be set in a specific value as true or false. 

